jackbridge (1.0-5) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Add ExecStartPre=wait-for-jack.sh before jackbridge-pin-route. jack.service is Type=simple, so After=jack.service only waits for jackd to fork — not for its server socket to accept clients. jackbridge-pi-up calls jack_load against jackd, which races socket readiness on a busy boot.

 -- Cam Gorrie <sastraxi@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 04:27:56 +0000

jackbridge (1.0-4) trixie; urgency=medium

  * jackbridge-pi-up: read /run/jackbridge.iface (set by
    jackbridge-pin-route ExecStartPre) as source of truth for the
    wired interface, falling back to $JACKBRIDGE_IFACE then eth0.
    Previously hardcoded to eth0, which breaks on boards with
    multiple wired NICs (Pi 5 + USB-C dongle, dual-port hubs).
  * jackbridge-pi-up: unload stale netadapter instances before
    loading a fresh one, so a failed prior ExecStop doesn't leave
    orphaned -01 instances that silently no-op the wiring.
  * jackbridge-pi-up: add 3-second delay between jack_unload and
    jack_load netadapter, giving the Mac's netmanager time to detect
    the socket error and clean up the stale JackNetMaster entry
    before the new SLAVE_AVAILABLE arrives. Without this, the new
    connection gets a -01 suffix and produces WriteResample /
    ringbuffer failure errors on the pi side and XRuns on both sides.
  * jackbridge-pi-down: iterate all netadapter* clients (not just
    netadapter), so stale -01 instances from failed prior runs are
    cleaned up on service stop.

 -- pi-gen-pistomp <noreply@github.com>  Sun, 28 Jun 2026 23:45:00 +0000

